This output confirms the actual situation clearly now.

Your storage stack itself is still on:

status.version: 4.18.17

even though:

odf-operator upgraded to 4.19.12

supporting operator bundles for 4.19.12 exist in catalog


So the ODF reconciliation that upgrades the StorageCluster-managed components has not happened yet.

The key line is:

VersionMatched
status: "False"
type: VersionMismatch

That means the operator currently thinks the deployed storage version matches the expected managed version (4.18.17), not 4.19.12.

This usually happens because the StorageCluster CR itself was never reconciled for a generation change after the operator upgrade.

You can trigger reconciliation safely.

First annotate the StorageCluster:

oc annotate storagecluster ocs-storagecluster -n openshift-storage force-reconcile=$(date +%s) --overwrite

Then restart the odf operator pod:

oc delete pod -n openshift-storage -l app.kubernetes.io/name=odf-operator-controller-manager

Now monitor:

oc get storagecluster -n openshift-storage -w

and:

oc get csv -A -w

and:

oc get installplan -A -w

What you expect:

StorageCluster version changes toward 4.19.12

new installplans appear

supporting operators move to 4.19.12-rhodf


Also watch Ceph health during rollout:

oc get cephcluster -n openshift-storage -w

Because this is a live storage upgrade, temporary:

Progressing=True

HEALTH_WARN


can occur during daemon restarts.

Do NOT manually delete old CSVs while this reconciliation is occurring.
